# Chapter 1 – Comments in Ruby

# This entire line is a comment. Ruby ignores it completely.
puts "This line runs and displays its text on screen."
puts "This runs too." # Everything after the hash symbol is ignored.
# puts "This entire puts call is commented out. It will not run."

=begin
This is a multi-line comment block.
Everything between the =begin and =end markers is completely ignored.
You can write as many lines of explanation here as you need.
=end

puts "This code runs normally after the comment block closes."
